Anthony Viljoen, AfriTin's CEO, and Laura Cornish, Editor of Mining Review Africa, speak about what AfriTin has planned for 2019 while he gives insight into operating environments in Namibia and South Africa. The company is on track to place its first tin concentrate into the market in Q4, 2019. Tin has been one of the better performing commodities on the London Metals Exchange of late with a global tin market anticipated to be valued at US$8.23 billion in 2023.